    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-26T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/7–2648: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic and Consular Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-26T01:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1948—1 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Resolution Jul 15 regarding renewal
                    truce in Palestine and Israel Dept considers acceptance by Israel and various
                    Arab states as unconditional. Dept considers differing views of Arabs and
                    Israelis re immigration and other matters are subjects for consideration by
                    Mediator and do not in any way invalidate truce.</p>
                <p>Sent to Baghdad, Cairo, Damascus, Beirut, Jidda, Amman, Jerusalem, Tel Aviv.</p>
                <p>Rptd to London for communication to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                    >FonOff</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
